# Performance Standards

## Frontend Performance
- Use React.memo() for expensive components that re-render frequently
- Implement proper code splitting with dynamic imports
- Use Next.js Image component for optimized image loading
- Implement proper lazy loading for below-the-fold content
- Use proper caching strategies for static assets

## Bundle Optimization
- Use proper tree shaking to eliminate dead code
- Implement proper code splitting at route and component levels
- Use dynamic imports for heavy libraries
- Optimize bundle size with proper webpack configuration
- Use proper compression (gzip/brotli) for assets

## Database Performance
- Use proper database indexing for frequently queried columns
- Implement proper query optimization and monitoring
- Use database connection pooling
- Implement proper caching strategies for database queries
- Use proper pagination for large datasets

## API Performance
- Implement proper response caching with appropriate TTL
- Use proper pagination for large API responses
- Implement proper rate limiting to prevent abuse
- Use proper compression for API responses
- Implement proper error handling without performance impact

## Image Optimization
- Use Next.js Image component with proper sizing
- Implement proper image formats (WebP, AVIF) with fallbacks
- Use proper lazy loading for images
- Implement proper responsive images
- Use proper image compression and optimization

## Caching Strategies
- Implement proper browser caching with appropriate headers
- Use proper CDN caching for static assets
- Implement proper application-level caching
- Use proper database query caching
- Implement proper API response caching

## Memory Management
- Implement proper cleanup in useEffect hooks
- Use proper event listener cleanup
- Implement proper memory leak prevention
- Use proper garbage collection optimization
- Monitor memory usage in production

## Network Optimization
- Use proper HTTP/2 and HTTP/3 when available
- Implement proper resource hints (preload, prefetch)
- Use proper service workers for offline functionality
- Implement proper compression for network requests
- Use proper connection pooling and keep-alive

## Core Web Vitals
- Optimize Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) < 2.5s
- Optimize First Input Delay (FID) < 100ms
- Optimize Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) < 0.1
- Use proper performance monitoring and alerting
- Implement proper performance budgets

## Monitoring & Analytics
- Use proper performance monitoring tools
- Implement proper real user monitoring (RUM)
- Use proper synthetic monitoring for critical paths
- Implement proper performance alerting
- Use proper performance analytics and reporting

## Development Performance
- Use proper development server optimization
- Implement proper hot module replacement (HMR)
- Use proper TypeScript compilation optimization
- Implement proper build time optimization
- Use proper development tooling optimization